	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118643"><p>Concorde not making airlines money was largely a myth - from about 1990 to its retirement, it was one of British Airways best profit centres.  Before then, British Airways was still operating under the agreements which carried over from when they were publicly owned, and Concorde was operated as a prestige thing first, revenue source second - when those agreements expired, BA jacked up the prices and found that their customer base didn't really notice, so operating Concorde became profitable.</p></div>
	</div>

