		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~NewtonsLaw">NewtonsLaw</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~NewtonsLaw">( 409638 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64118927"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118927"><p>Yes, there are *many* challenges... not the least of which is that of reliably sustaining the detonation.  Think of it as trying to keep a candle lit in a hurricane.</p><p>It took a long time for researchers to produce an RDE that would run for more than a few short seconds without stopping, due to the precarious nature of the rotating shock wave and its sensitivity to pressure/density, temperature and other factors.</p><p>Going from "we got it working" to "we have a commercially viable product in production" is a huge s<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64118927">

</div>
